00:11:50.747 --> 00:11:54.687
what is your identity.

00:11:55.139 --> 00:11:59.335
So we take to religions.

00:12:00.501 --> 00:12:03.528
But in the modern times, religions have become

00:12:03.736 --> 00:12:07.751
money oriented or power oriented.

00:12:09.542 --> 00:12:18.337
Also, it was great incarnations who came

00:12:18.538 --> 00:12:23.710
like Christ, Mohammed Saab, Moses.

00:12:23.911 --> 00:12:29.623
They were very great, pure incarnations

00:12:30.509 --> 00:12:33.747
and they did not know what sort of people they were facing.

00:12:33.948 --> 00:12:38.260
The way they were tortured and crucified.

00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:44.342
They preached to people who cannot follow their followings,

00:12:44.543 --> 00:12:48.875
they cannot follow their principles.

00:12:50.336 --> 00:12:54.251
For example, Christ has said in the fifth chapter  Mathews

00:12:54.475 --> 00:13:00.162
that if your one eye commits a sin, you take out the eye.

00:13:01.538 --> 00:13:07.835
If your one hand does some sinful thing, you cut out the hand.

00:13:08.036 --> 00:13:12.794
If somebody slaps you on this face, turn the other face.

00:13:13.927 --> 00:13:19.185
I haven't seen any Christian without eye and without hands.

00:13:20.943 --> 00:13:26.364
It's an impossible thing and very difficult.

00:13:27.958 --> 00:13:33.872
It was easy for Christ to say that because He was so great.

00:13:34.339 --> 00:13:41.978
Actually, you have to become a saint to follow His principles.

00:13:42.690 --> 00:13:47.255
Ordinary people cannot follow Him.

00:13:47.927 --> 00:13:50.922
Then I think Mohammed Saab thought that He was so strict

00:13:51.131 --> 00:13:59.004
with the men, so He made lots of laws for the women also.

00:13:59.963 --> 00:14:05.482
